1
00:02:39,280 --> 00:02:40,520
{\an8}Aru, gorgeous!

2
00:02:42,640 --> 00:02:44,440
{\an8}I can do a lot worse than that.

3
00:02:44,520 --> 00:02:46,160
{\an8}The bullets were directed at me only.

4
00:02:46,240 --> 00:02:47,440
{\an8}Who do you think did it?

5
00:02:47,520 --> 00:02:49,760
{\an8}I don't know. Do you?

6
00:02:50,560 --> 00:02:52,240
{\an8}My dad died because of Fire Phoenix.

7
00:02:52,320 --> 00:02:54,200
{\an8}Then why aren’t you searching
for the truth?

8
00:02:54,280 --> 00:02:55,680
{\an8}<i>The mask contains</i>

9
00:02:55,760 --> 00:02:58,240
{\an8}<i>the code to all the information</i>
<i>of every member.</i>

10
00:02:58,320 --> 00:03:00,000
{\an8}<i>If we can steal Naruban's mask,</i>

11
00:03:00,080 --> 00:03:02,720
{\an8}then we can get
to the core of Fire Phoenix.

12
00:03:36,800 --> 00:03:38,000
Can you disable the cameras?

13
00:04:32,160 --> 00:04:34,880
I can't hack it. There are
too many layers of encryption.

14
00:04:34,960 --> 00:04:37,880
I think you'd better get out of there.

15
00:04:48,840 --> 00:04:50,520
The restroom's not on this floor.

16
00:04:53,760 --> 00:04:55,560
What are you doing up here?

17
00:04:58,320 --> 00:05:00,240
What'd you plan to do in my house?

18
00:05:04,760 --> 00:05:06,720
What the hell
are you trying to find here?!

19
00:05:06,800 --> 00:05:07,680
Huh?!

20
00:05:29,240 --> 00:05:30,360
Are you crazy?!

21
00:05:30,440 --> 00:05:32,640
I'm not. You're the one who's crazy!

22
00:05:32,720 --> 00:05:34,000
You're so crazy over him

23
00:05:34,080 --> 00:05:36,960
that you can't even see
he only came to go to Dad's room.

24
00:05:38,680 --> 00:05:42,520
You can't fool me. We installed
security cameras from every angle.

25
00:05:43,360 --> 00:05:44,400
What happened?

26
00:06:09,640 --> 00:06:10,920
See, Mom? He's a scumbag!

27
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:14,520
He clearly came to 3C with an agenda.

28
00:06:14,600 --> 00:06:15,600
Throw him out.

29
00:06:16,560 --> 00:06:18,720
Nun, take your brother outside for a bit.

30
00:06:21,040 --> 00:06:24,080
Can't you see?
He's trying to go into Dad's room!

31
00:06:24,160 --> 00:06:26,240
I saw him just standing still.

32
00:06:30,600 --> 00:06:33,200
No. He wasn't standing there!

33
00:06:33,280 --> 00:06:34,480
Techut.

34
00:06:39,680 --> 00:06:43,160
I'm sorry for all the fuss
and the misunderstanding.

35
00:06:44,120 --> 00:06:46,000
Taiga, let's leave.

36
00:06:47,760 --> 00:06:49,440
I just got out of the restroom.

37
00:06:49,520 --> 00:06:52,120
I noticed the decorating style here,
so I looked around.

38
00:06:52,840 --> 00:06:53,880
I'm sorry.

39
00:06:57,760 --> 00:07:01,160
We'll get going now.
Let's discuss cooking again.

40
00:07:01,240 --> 00:07:02,120
That was fun.

41
00:07:06,440 --> 00:07:09,080
Taiga's lying. I saw it with my own eyes.

42
00:07:16,200 --> 00:07:17,800
No matter where Mr. Taiga goes,

43
00:07:17,880 --> 00:07:19,960
he's still our guest.

44
00:07:20,040 --> 00:07:22,800
We still need to work with him
and rely on his reputation.

45
00:07:23,320 --> 00:07:27,720
Next time, don't run your mouth
unless you've got irrefutable proof.

46
00:07:41,520 --> 00:07:42,880
It's okay.

47
00:07:43,400 --> 00:07:45,760
I still have my café as a front
in their building,

48
00:07:45,840 --> 00:07:49,120
and my dad's about to buy up 3C's shares.

49
00:07:50,280 --> 00:07:53,200
Soon, I might even get an office
next to Naruban's.

50
00:07:55,560 --> 00:07:56,560
Hey,

51
00:07:56,640 --> 00:07:58,880
can I have one of the floors, then?

52
00:07:58,960 --> 00:08:00,560
I want to lie down and chill there.

53
00:08:03,440 --> 00:08:04,720
Who on earth would give you one?

54
00:08:05,720 --> 00:08:09,120
You, madam. I just need one floor.
Don't be so stingy.

55
00:08:09,800 --> 00:08:12,520
Or are you fake rich? Faking your wealth?

56
00:08:12,600 --> 00:08:14,960
You're just faking it, aren't you?

57
00:08:29,920 --> 00:08:31,320
These are the files my Dad kept.

58
00:08:34,679 --> 00:08:36,039
FAMILY BRUTALLY SHOT
MULTIPLE TIMES AND KILLED IN AMBUSH

59
00:08:36,120 --> 00:08:37,360
3C'S CO-FOUNDER AND HIS FAMILY
WERE CHASED DOWN, SHOT, AND KILLED

60
00:08:38,039 --> 00:08:39,919
What about the other files
besides Prin's case?

61
00:08:40,720 --> 00:08:43,600
I tried to open them.
Some of them required a password.

62
00:08:49,920 --> 00:08:53,160
Give me the hard drive. I'll open them.

63
00:09:20,040 --> 00:09:21,520
Uncle Punlop, run!

64
00:10:20,480 --> 00:10:21,520
Taiga!

65
00:10:23,840 --> 00:10:24,760
Stop moving.

66
00:10:26,320 --> 00:10:27,240
Let's go.

67
00:10:46,840 --> 00:10:48,600
You won't get lucky every time, Rin!

68
00:10:53,760 --> 00:10:54,800
N - ALL FIRE PHOENIX CASE FILES

69
00:10:57,160 --> 00:10:58,080
ALL FIRE PHOENIX CASE FILES 2

70
00:11:03,160 --> 00:11:05,400
Thank God you got there in time,

71
00:11:06,120 --> 00:11:08,680
but it won't be easy
to tap her calls next time.

72
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:13,920
Don't let anyone come.
Don't let anyone find me and Rin.

73
00:11:14,760 --> 00:11:17,000
Turn off both your phone and Rin's.

74
00:11:17,960 --> 00:11:20,720
I'll go talk to Aru. We'll need her help.

75
00:11:22,520 --> 00:11:24,160
Deal with Ratee for me.

76
00:11:26,600 --> 00:11:29,240
Change the code
on all the doors in the house too.

77
00:11:29,880 --> 00:11:32,680
I'll tell Ratee you're drawing
somewhere out of town.

78
00:11:33,200 --> 00:11:34,320
Thanks.

79
00:11:42,640 --> 00:11:44,000
Dhammatat,

80
00:11:44,720 --> 00:11:48,200
don't contact me.
I'll find a way to contact you myself.

81
00:11:59,560 --> 00:12:00,680
How are you feeling?

82
00:12:01,600 --> 00:12:03,040
Just hurry up and do it.

83
00:12:13,080 --> 00:12:14,000
Ready?

84
00:12:32,800 --> 00:12:34,120
Rin!

85
00:13:20,920 --> 00:13:22,040
Why are you here?

86
00:13:23,360 --> 00:13:25,080
I just wanted to talk to you, Aru.

87
00:13:25,680 --> 00:13:30,040
This is my workplace.
Don't bother me like this again.

88
00:13:30,120 --> 00:13:31,480
I'm sorry.

89
00:13:35,280 --> 00:13:37,040
Do you want to have dinner sometime?

90
00:13:45,400 --> 00:13:48,760
I'm busy, Sun. Just leave.

91
00:13:53,640 --> 00:13:55,560
Anyway, I should get back to work.

92
00:14:34,440 --> 00:14:37,400
Don't worry about Rin.
Taiga's taking care of her.

93
00:14:37,920 --> 00:14:40,440
We should call the police!

94
00:14:41,960 --> 00:14:44,240
I don't think Rin would want that.

95
00:14:46,240 --> 00:14:49,960
Don't go home yet.
If you see a stranger lurking around,

96
00:14:50,040 --> 00:14:52,720
call me right away.
Or just call the police,

97
00:14:53,480 --> 00:14:56,680
because right now,
they'll target you for sure.

98
00:14:57,320 --> 00:14:58,760
Who?

99
00:15:09,760 --> 00:15:13,200
I'm not sure either,
but better safe than sorry.

100
00:15:17,360 --> 00:15:19,800
It's really serious, isn't it?

101
00:15:25,800 --> 00:15:29,440
Just wait for Rin to recover.
Taiga will let us know.

102
00:15:39,680 --> 00:15:44,160
Rin will be just fine. Taiga will take
great care of her for sure.

103
00:17:21,040 --> 00:17:24,560
Taiga's an artist.
When he works on his art,

104
00:17:25,400 --> 00:17:28,160
he likes to get away from annoying people.

105
00:17:30,440 --> 00:17:32,320
At least, he should've called me.

106
00:17:35,680 --> 00:17:38,520
If he didn't call,
it's because he didn't want to.

107
00:17:43,880 --> 00:17:46,880
Right now, he might be drawing
in some forest,

108
00:17:47,840 --> 00:17:51,600
maybe Bali, Brazil, New Zealand,

109
00:17:52,760 --> 00:17:55,560
or maybe he's back in Japan now.

110
00:17:55,640 --> 00:17:57,200
So where is he, really?

111
00:17:57,720 --> 00:17:59,080
Who is he to you?

112
00:17:59,160 --> 00:18:02,400
Are you two just friends,
or more than that?

113
00:18:03,080 --> 00:18:05,280
Why are you getting involved
in his business?

114
00:18:06,640 --> 00:18:08,040
If you can't take it,

115
00:18:08,640 --> 00:18:12,840
then stop working with him.
Easy. End of story.

116
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:16,640
When you can reach him,

117
00:18:17,480 --> 00:18:20,960
tell him I need to discuss work with him.

118
00:18:31,920 --> 00:18:33,640
Even if I knew, I'd never tell you.

119
00:18:38,280 --> 00:18:39,480
Damn you, Dhammatat!

120
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:42,760
You'd better not be helping Taiga
lie to me.

121
00:22:35,360 --> 00:22:39,040
Medical Sciences.
Your education's not bad.

122
00:22:39,560 --> 00:22:43,640
I can do any job,
even if it's unrelated to my degree.

123
00:22:50,000 --> 00:22:54,520
What if I can offer you a job
that's related to your degree?

124
00:22:55,440 --> 00:22:56,640
I'd do it.

125
00:22:59,520 --> 00:23:00,720
Are you scared of me?

126
00:23:02,160 --> 00:23:04,720
I'll put you on the job you're capable of,

127
00:23:04,800 --> 00:23:09,280
and if you want to keep your job at 3C
for a long time, you have to do it well.

128
00:24:00,880 --> 00:24:02,280
You changed my clothes?

129
00:24:06,920 --> 00:24:09,320
I had a nurse take care of your wound
and change your clothes.

130
00:24:13,520 --> 00:24:14,600
Does it still hurt?

131
00:24:16,600 --> 00:24:17,720
A little bit.

132
00:24:17,800 --> 00:24:19,240
You got shot.

133
00:24:19,760 --> 00:24:21,320
I don't know who did it.

134
00:24:43,200 --> 00:24:44,520
Your fever's down.

135
00:24:51,440 --> 00:24:54,600
What's the hurry?
You haven't eaten breakfast yet.

136
00:24:55,120 --> 00:24:57,280
- I'm not hungry.
- You still need to eat,

137
00:24:57,360 --> 00:24:58,960
so you can take your medicine.

138
00:24:59,560 --> 00:25:01,960
I made it for you. You have to eat it.

139
00:25:11,560 --> 00:25:13,680
I carried you through gunfire
to bring you here,

140
00:25:16,000 --> 00:25:17,600
you think I'd poison you?

141
00:25:22,080 --> 00:25:23,640
I don't like rice soup.

142
00:25:25,800 --> 00:25:27,360
Don't like rice soup?

143
00:25:32,200 --> 00:25:33,480
Or do you want me to feed you?

144
00:25:41,240 --> 00:25:43,200
You can't contact Mr. Taiga at all?

145
00:25:43,720 --> 00:25:46,200
He's just suddenly gone without a trace.

146
00:25:46,960 --> 00:25:50,160
He turned off his phone too.
Even the team doesn't know where he is.

147
00:25:51,040 --> 00:25:54,440
That's just the way artists are.
Bear with him, okay?

148
00:25:54,520 --> 00:25:56,600
Why am I the one
who has to put up with him, Mom?

149
00:25:57,640 --> 00:25:59,920
Because you love him
more than he loves you.

150
00:26:01,040 --> 00:26:04,840
That's why Mr. Taiga
always has the edge on you.

151
00:26:06,040 --> 00:26:09,000
You mix your work and personal life.

152
00:26:11,440 --> 00:26:12,520
Be a little more patient.

153
00:26:13,040 --> 00:26:15,840
I want you to see every side of him first.

154
00:26:16,600 --> 00:26:20,320
You think he's hiding something from us?

155
00:26:20,400 --> 00:26:22,640
If you learn the truth yourself,

156
00:26:23,680 --> 00:26:24,920
you'll be happy

157
00:26:25,560 --> 00:26:28,680
to know the man you love
better than anyone.

158
00:26:44,720 --> 00:26:48,080
Why can't I contact anyone?
Have they all run off to Mars?

159
00:27:26,200 --> 00:27:27,840
Ugh.

160
00:27:28,720 --> 00:27:30,840
Here to find your people too, Chief?

161
00:27:34,160 --> 00:27:35,880
And you're looking for revenge on me.

162
00:27:38,280 --> 00:27:40,240
Killing me here wouldn't be wise, no?

163
00:27:41,520 --> 00:27:42,680
I'm sure you know

164
00:27:44,080 --> 00:27:47,440
I won't kill you until I've gathered
everything to expose Fire Phoenix.

165
00:27:49,000 --> 00:27:50,840
Fire Phoenix won't fall

166
00:27:51,840 --> 00:27:53,560
just because of me alone.

167
00:27:55,520 --> 00:27:56,880
Who's Damon,

168
00:27:57,400 --> 00:28:00,240
the leader of Fire Phoenix? Where's Damon?

169
00:28:01,240 --> 00:28:02,360
Who are you people?

170
00:28:03,280 --> 00:28:04,360
What are you doing here?

171
00:28:19,040 --> 00:28:20,160
Ugh.

172
00:28:26,360 --> 00:28:30,040
Security? We've got intruders
in the building. Please catch them!

173
00:28:49,200 --> 00:28:53,120
Prin's whole family died.
Now the police will suspect me for sure.

174
00:28:56,920 --> 00:28:59,200
A guy like you would never kill a friend.

175
00:28:59,720 --> 00:29:04,240
I'm sure you'd never kill
a close friend like Prin.

176
00:29:14,360 --> 00:29:15,480
Mom,

177
00:29:16,760 --> 00:29:18,520
we couldn't find those two.

178
00:29:21,000 --> 00:29:23,480
Are you alright, Mom?

179
00:29:23,560 --> 00:29:24,920
I'm fine.

180
00:29:25,800 --> 00:29:28,760
I'm going to kill them. They hurt you!

181
00:29:28,840 --> 00:29:29,920
Calm down.

182
00:29:30,000 --> 00:29:32,880
I'm sending the footage to the police.
We'll surely catch them.

183
00:29:49,680 --> 00:29:50,880
Does it still hurt?

184
00:30:03,000 --> 00:30:04,200
Please eat up.

185
00:30:18,000 --> 00:30:19,320
You should eat up too.

186
00:30:23,040 --> 00:30:25,160
I haven't told anyone I'm here.

187
00:30:31,120 --> 00:30:33,000
You can stay here as long as you want.

188
00:31:03,320 --> 00:31:04,640
You can sleep here.

189
00:31:06,800 --> 00:31:08,320
I'll sleep here too.

190
00:31:17,680 --> 00:31:18,680
Let go of me.

191
00:31:20,080 --> 00:31:23,600
Last night, I lay here and held you.

192
00:31:27,160 --> 00:31:28,560
You had a fever.

193
00:31:31,320 --> 00:31:32,480
I'm fine now.

194
00:38:39,320 --> 00:38:41,520
Blazing Tiger. They're a gang in Japan.

195
00:38:42,040 --> 00:38:45,640
They oppose Fire Phoenix,
and they've killed our people.

196
00:38:48,160 --> 00:38:51,280
Fire Phoenix will wipe them out.

197
00:38:51,360 --> 00:38:53,400
We'll make sure no one survives.

198
00:39:26,840 --> 00:39:27,800
Where are you going?

199
00:39:30,920 --> 00:39:32,680
I need to go back to work.

200
00:39:37,400 --> 00:39:38,400
Ow!

201
00:39:46,680 --> 00:39:48,400
Who gave you permission?

202
00:39:49,040 --> 00:39:50,440
I did.

203
00:40:00,800 --> 00:40:02,400
If I don't give you permission…

204
00:40:15,600 --> 00:40:16,880
Want to kill me?

205
00:40:22,320 --> 00:40:23,400
Do it then!

206
00:40:25,040 --> 00:40:26,120
Do it.

207
00:40:27,840 --> 00:40:29,600
Your job is to kill me anyway.

208
00:41:16,240 --> 00:41:18,160
I'm sending you back to 3C.

209
00:41:19,880 --> 00:41:22,160
We'll act like nothing happened here.

210
00:41:23,560 --> 00:41:28,400
I'm just a designer,
and you just work for 3C.

211
00:41:31,880 --> 00:41:34,000
And if you still want to kill me,

212
00:41:35,120 --> 00:41:36,440
go ahead.

213
00:42:01,600 --> 00:42:05,400
I'll make it so that 3C-Coins can be used
to buy everything on the Hi app.

214
00:42:06,920 --> 00:42:11,400
I'll make sure our coin is the only
digital currency people can use.

215
00:42:13,440 --> 00:42:17,320
Find a way to make every feature
on the Hi app indispensable to everyone.

216
00:42:18,440 --> 00:42:19,840
Every single feature.

217
00:42:19,920 --> 00:42:24,560
3C needs to be like breath,
the very thing people depend on.

218
00:42:25,160 --> 00:42:26,120
Got it.

219
00:42:43,560 --> 00:42:45,440
You know Rin is part of Fire Phoenix,

220
00:42:46,680 --> 00:42:49,960
and she knows you aren't just a designer.

221
00:42:51,280 --> 00:42:52,680
I can't kill her.

222
00:42:54,240 --> 00:42:56,680
Sometimes death isn't the solution.

223
00:42:58,520 --> 00:42:59,880
You did the right thing.

224
00:43:02,400 --> 00:43:06,240
She holds some very important information.
That's why she's being hunted.

225
00:43:07,320 --> 00:43:10,120
You know who was gunning her down, right?

226
00:43:12,160 --> 00:43:13,160
It was Khanin.

227
00:43:13,880 --> 00:43:14,960
Yes.

228
00:43:16,120 --> 00:43:18,760
I could hack one of the cameras
in the warehouse.

229
00:43:25,480 --> 00:43:29,080
Looks like Rin isn't your only target.

230
00:43:32,280 --> 00:43:33,680
Watch the previous video.

231
00:43:39,680 --> 00:43:41,040
Who's that man?

232
00:43:43,360 --> 00:43:45,200
Chief Inspector Punlop,

233
00:43:45,720 --> 00:43:48,160
a chief who was famous
for busting a human trafficking ring.

234
00:43:48,800 --> 00:43:50,640
After that, he disappeared for a while

235
00:43:50,720 --> 00:43:53,880
before quickly getting promoted
and moving into policy work.

236
00:43:55,880 --> 00:43:57,680
But a reliable source says

237
00:43:57,760 --> 00:44:00,800
that he's tied
to several secret operations.

238
00:44:06,560 --> 00:44:10,640
Don't ever mention those two people,
no matter who asks.

239
00:44:12,600 --> 00:44:16,600
Madam Ratee and Aru are the only ones
who'd be desperate to know.

240
00:44:18,840 --> 00:44:20,200
You should be careful too.

241
00:44:21,560 --> 00:44:25,480
Even when Rin's back,
everyone will want to know

242
00:44:26,120 --> 00:44:27,800
who took her away to hide.

243
00:44:36,920 --> 00:44:39,920
{\an8}Techut rushed to set up the department
and took control of everything.

244
00:44:40,600 --> 00:44:43,440
{\an8}<i>Find the hard drive.</i>
<i>If anyone gets in the way…</i>

245
00:44:44,520 --> 00:44:45,840
{\an8}…just kill them all.

246
00:44:52,480 --> 00:44:54,320
{\an8}- <i>Thank you.</i>
- <i>I only helped you</i>

247
00:44:54,400 --> 00:44:56,400
{\an8}<i>because you're still useful to me.</i>

248
00:45:29,320 --> 00:45:31,720
Subtitle translation by:
Ramil Natnitiwitaya

